messages.messageBody:
On Tue, 5 Feb 2002 21:12:32 -0800 (PST) meghan anderson
<moonmeghan@...> writes:
>I'm searching for more
> work (that I can do from home),

Ebay!

I keep thinking that once we move back to California, I can hit all the
thrift stores in the small towns and find so much cool stuff to ebay.
There used to be a thrift store in Grass Valley, it closed a couple of
years ago but I went when I was teaching and filled two garbage bags full
of stuff for my kids for $5...toys, books, stuff like that, cool stuff.
It was awesome.

Cacie is getting really good at finding stuff to ebay, it's quite cool. I
give her half the profit on stuff she finds, or she can buy it herself
and I'll help her list it and she gets all the profit. Between her
allowance, the money she made off a brownie outfit and some Barney
videos, money she made selling doughnuts at our yard sale, and money she
made just selling her stuff at our yard sale, she's up to $30 saved,
which is just amazing her.. generally money runs through her fingers like
water.

She did say yesterday that she wants to buy a rocking horse for a
friend's birthday next month, they were talking on the phone and her
friend said she wanted one. She's like that...

I'm open to other money-making ideas, though.

Dar
